quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  26,178,"Indeed, I am to you a trustworthy messenger."
  26,179,"So fear Allāh and obey me."
  26,180,"And I do not ask you for it any payment. My payment is only from the Lord of the worlds."
  33,31,"And whoever of you devoutly obeys Allāh and His Messenger and does righteousness - We will give her her reward twice; and We have prepared for her a noble provision."
  33,32,"O wives of the Prophet, you are not like anyone among women. If you fear Allāh, then do not be soft in speech [to men],{1} lest he in whose heart is disease should covet, but speak with appropriate speech.",1:[The meaning has also been given as "You are not like any among women if you fear Allāh.  So do not be soft in speech..."]
  33,33,"And abide in your houses and do not display yourselves as [was] the display of the former times of ignorance. And establish prayer and give zakāh and obey Allāh and His Messenger. Allāh intends only to remove from you the impurity [of sin], O people of the [Prophet's] household, and to purify you with [extensive] purification."
  34,10,"And We certainly gave David from Us bounty. [We said], "
  34,11,"[Commanding him], "
  34,12,"And to Solomon [We subjected] the wind - its morning [journey was that of] a month - and its afternoon [journey was that of] a month, and We made flow for him a spring of [liquid] copper. And among the jinn were those who worked for him by the permission of his Lord. And whoever deviated among them from Our command - We will make him taste of the punishment of the Blaze."